com.facebook.buck.android

Class PreDexMerge

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.rules.AbstractBuildable
      • com.facebook.buck.android.PreDexMerge
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Buildable, InitializableFromDisk<com.facebook.buck.android.PreDexMerge.BuildOutput>

    public class PreDexMerge
extends AbstractBuildable
implements InitializableFromDisk<com.facebook.buck.android.PreDexMerge.BuildOutput>
    Buildable that is responsible for:
    • Bucketing pre-dexed jars into lists for primary and secondary dex files (if the app is split-dex).
    • Merging the pre-dexed jars into primary and secondary dex files.
    • Writing the split-dex "metadata.txt".

    Clients of this Buildable may need to know:

    • The locations of the zip files directories containing secondary dex files and metadata.
    This uses a separate implementation from addDexingSteps. The differences in the splitting logic are too significant to make it worth merging them.

        Get the set of input files whose contents should be hashed for the purpose of determining whether this rule is cached.

        Note that inputs are iterable and should generally be alphabetized so that lists with the same elements will be .equals() to one another.
